A 46-year-old female presented with fatigue, joint pain, and a facial rash across both cheeks for two months. ANA was positive at 1:1280 homogeneous pattern. Anti-double-stranded DNA antibody was elevated at 248 IU/mL. Complement levels were low with C3 of 48 mg/dL and C4 of 6 mg/dL. Complete blood count showed WBC 2,600 with lymphocyte count of 800. Urinalysis revealed 2+ protein and 15 RBCs per high-power field. A 24-hour urine collection showed 2.1 g of protein. Renal biopsy was performed and histopathology demonstrated class IV diffuse proliferative lupus nephritis with crescentic changes. She was started on mycophenolate mofetil and pulse-dose methylprednisolone followed by oral prednisone taper.

